Amanda Burton To Marco and anyone else who supports watching child porn because watching it doesn't promote it: Do you know how porn websites make money? The majority of their money is NOT from people paying for services. It's from advertisements. If you don't know how showing advertisements bring in money to websites, look it up. People who go on these websites don't have to pay ANYTHING to bring in money for porn websites. These websites keep track of what is making money for them- i.e. what porn videos are getting the most views, and therefore, which advertisements are making the most money. Nothing exists without a demand for it. When people watch child porn, that creates a demand. And if viewership of a particular type of porn rises, they see that and then they meet the demand. If nobody watched child porn, there wouldn't be a demand. So the simple fact that there is a demand for child porn will inevitably lead to child porn being created. If the demand is eradicated-- if pedophiles are caught and sent to jail or something, or if it is markedly more difficult to have access to through more strictly enforced laws, then making the product will bring in less money and porn companies will do it less. In conclusion, watching child porn DOES promote it through supply-and-demand economics.
